						<div class="postbody">I usually use BSNES for play testing, but SNES9X for YouTube videos, but it sounds like SNES9x doesn't do good pitch modulation.  Am I just using an outdated emulator, or is SNES9x still like that.  Or is pitch modulation supposed to sound like that, and BSNES sounds wrong?</div>

