					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Kega Fusion uses a custom codec that essentially just stores whatever data is written to the video chips, resulting in really tiny lossless files and no meaningful extra CPU power during recording. When done you convert the file over with your favorite video processing software. That's probably a bit more work on software side (new video codec creation is probably not straightforward) than creating and then recording keylogs into a video.</div>

					
