						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Kismet wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">youtube will always transcode that to aac.<br /></div>And vorbis. And opus. And you don't know which encoding or bitrate the viewer will get.<br /><br />Chiptunes are a particularly bad match to any lossy codec at all; with some I can pass an ABX test even at bitrates well above the nominal &quot;normal&quot; audio &quot;transparency&quot; bitrate. The only conclusion I can come to, since you can't specify the codec, is to just not worry about it much.</div>

